# SmartRecruit — Backend Project Rules

## Project Overview
SmartRecruit adalah platform manajemen rekrutmen berbasis web dengan AI screening CV otomatis.
Tech stack: Node.js + Express.js + MongoDB (Mongoose) + JWT + Cloudinary + OpenAI API + Nodemailer.

## Folder Structure
- controllers/  → logic handler per resource
- routes/       → Express route definitions
- models/       → Mongoose schema (User, JobPosting, Candidate)
- middleware/   → authMiddleware (JWT), errorHandler, uploadMiddleware (Multer)
- services/     → aiService (OpenAI), emailService (Nodemailer), storageService (Cloudinary)
- jobs/         → screeningJob.js (background AI screening, non-blocking)
- config/       → db.js (MongoDB), cloudinary.js

## Database Collections
1. users        → HR Admin only (no public register). Fields: name, email, password (bcrypt), role, createdAt
2. jobpostings  → Fields: title, aboutPosition, description, requirements, location, employmentType (Full-time/Part-time/Internship), status (open/closed), createdBy (ref: users), createdAt
3. candidates   → Fields: name, email, phone, jobId (ref: jobpostings), cvUrl, aiScore (0-100), aiStrengths, aiWeaknesses, aiFeedback, status (pending/processed/advanced/rejected/failed), appliedAt

## API Endpoints

### AUTH (no JWT required)
POST   /api/auth/login
POST   /api/auth/logout           ← requires JWT
PUT    /api/auth/change-password  ← requires JWT

### PUBLIC (no JWT required)
GET    /api/jobs                  ← query: ?search= &location= &employmentType=
GET    /api/jobs/:id
POST   /api/jobs/:id/apply        ← upload CV (PDF), triggers AI screening in background

### HR DASHBOARD (JWT required)
GET    /api/dashboard/stats       ← total jobs, total candidates, pending, advanced

### CANDIDATES (JWT required)
GET    /api/candidates            ← filter: ?jobId= &status=
GET    /api/candidates/:id
PUT    /api/candidates/:id/accept ← update status to "advanced", send accept email
PUT    /api/candidates/:id/reject ← generate AI feedback, update status to "rejected", send reject email

### JOB POSTINGS - HR (JWT required)
GET    /api/hr/jobs
POST   /api/hr/jobs
PUT    /api/hr/jobs/:id
DELETE /api/hr/jobs/:id
PATCH  /api/hr/jobs/:id/status    ← toggle open/closed

## Key Business Logic
1. AI Screening adalah ASYNC (background process) — kandidat submit → simpan dengan status "pending" → trigger screeningJob → update hasil ke DB
2. Polling dari frontend setiap 5-10 detik untuk refresh data kandidat
3. CV disimpan di Cloudinary, hanya URL (cvUrl) yang disimpan di DB
4. storageService.js adalah abstraction layer — bisa switch antara Cloudinary dan local storage
5. Email dikirim otomatis saat HR klik Accept atau Reject
6. Reject → OpenAI generate feedback personal dulu → baru kirim email

## Coding Conventions
- Gunakan async/await, bukan callback
- Semua error di-throw ke errorHandler middleware menggunakan next(error)
- Response format konsisten: { success: true/false, data: {}, message: "" }
- JWT secret dari process.env.JWT_SECRET
- Semua nilai sensitif dari .env, jangan hardcode
- Gunakan bcryptjs (bukan bcrypt) untuk hash password

## Environment Variables yang Digunakan
PORT, MONGO_URI, JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRES_IN,
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME, CLOUDINARY_API_KEY, CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET,
OPENAI_API_KEY,
EMAIL_USER, EMAIL_PASS, EMAIL_FROM
```

---

### Langkah 3 — Load Rules di Antigravity

1. Buka folder `smartrecruit-backend` di Antigravity
2. Masuk ke **Settings** → **Rules** → **Add Project Rules**
3. Arahkan ke file `.agyrules` yang sudah dibuat
4. Atau Antigravity biasanya **auto-detect** file `.agyrules` di root folder

---

### Langkah 4 — Cara Memberi Instruksi ke Agent

Setelah rules ter-load, kamu bisa langsung perintahkan agent dengan natural language, contoh:
```
"Buatkan models/User.js sesuai schema di project rules"

"Implementasikan POST /api/auth/login di authController.js 
dan authRoutes.js sesuai konvensi project"

"Buat screeningJob.js yang memanggil aiService untuk 
analisis CV secara background process"
